{
  "texts": [
    "Singh et al. [103] noted that SCBA increases calcium hydroxide consumption, which enhances resistance to chloride penetration and reduces permeability by resulting in a denser microstructure.",
    "Jha et al. [107] observed that a 10% SCBA replacement improved pore structure and decreased permeability, although higher replacement levels increased porosity due to larger SCBA particles.",
    "Rajasekar et al. [108] and Zareei et al.",
    "[109] further confirmed that SCBA contributes to more C-S-H gel formation and reduced porosity, highlighting its role in densifying the concrete matrix and improving the ITZ.",
    "The SEM image in Fig. 15 illustrates the impact of (SCBA) on the concrete microstructure."
  ]
}